item.title: Betaflight Has No Autotune â€” So I Built One
item.description:
The PID Tuning Loop Every FPV Pilot Knows
If you fly FPV, you've been through this cycle: Fly a pack. Notice oscillations on descents. Land. Plug in USB. Open Betaflight Configurator. Stare at P, I, D sliders. Which one do I change? By how much? Guess. Flash. Fly again. Still not right. Repeat. This loop can eat hours â€” sometimes days. And even experienced pilots admit that PID tuning is more art than science. You're basically doing gradient descent by hand, one flight at a time. Pilots have been asking for years. There's a GitHub issue (#6857) with hundreds of comments requesting autotune.

Stop Building Humanoid Agents: The Case for "Octopus Architecture"
item.description: We are currently in the "Day 1" era of AI coding agents. The standard architecture for tools like AutoGPT or typical LangChain implementations looks something like this: Central Brain (LLM) makes a plan. Brain issues a command (e.g., write_file). System executes command. System returns output (or error). Brain reads error, thinks, plans a fix, and issues a new command. This is the Humanoid Model. It assumes a central intelligence must micro-manage every movement of its limbs. It is also terribly inefficient.
